A) I use the remote rather than stdio versions of GitHub MCP and Context7
B) I don't mind the loss of Sequential-Thinking local-only (stdio) plugin for Claude Code CLI (on MBP)
C) I export work on the MBP via `&` prefix

The concern that became obvious was would the CLAUDE.md be ignored, or would it cause errors due to additionals not supported on some of the devices (like the non-negotiable mandates to use Sequential-Thinking and Plan mode by-default. Says it'd still be read, but selective-application of instructions based on relevance would happen. So no erroring out. 

So, definitely some degradation but nothing materially significant enough to stop the workflow or cause crashing.
